.TH HELLO_FORTRAN 1 "" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hello_fortran \- recovered Fortran "hello world" program, re-expressed in C
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hello_fortran
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hello_fortran
is a small program recovered from the binary
.IR hello-gfortran-O2 ,
which was originally written in Fortran and compiled with
.B gfortran
at optimization level
.BR -O2 .
The recovered source is provided in C, split into a C entry point
.RB ( main.c )
that delegates to a Fortran-style main program body
.RB ( hello.c )
containing the translated program logic.
.PP
When run, the program executes the body of the original Fortran
.B PROGRAM
unit and exits.
.SH OPTIONS
.B hello_fortran
does not define any command-line options. Any arguments accepted on
the command line are those handled by the standard program startup
path inherited from the recovered entry point; no option is
documented as part of the program's own interface.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gfortran (1),
.BR cmake (1),
.BR cc (1)
